# Frontend Structure Rules

## Feature folder layout

```
apps/web/src/features/<domain>/
  components/
    <ComponentName>/        ← one folder per component
      <ComponentName>.tsx
      <ComponentName>.css
      index.ts
  hooks/                    ← useXxx.ts files
  pages/
    <PageName>/
      <PageName>.tsx
      <PageName>.css
      index.ts
  api/
    <domain>ApiClient.ts    ← typed HTTP functions only
  types.ts                  ← TS types/interfaces for this domain
  index.ts                  ← public exports only
```

## Shared component placement decision

| Condition | Location |
|---|---|
| Used by 2+ features OR has no domain knowledge | `shared/components/<Name>/` |
| Domain-specific (imports from a feature type) | `features/<domain>/components/<Name>/` |
| Internal to one component (e.g. DrawerTabBar inside ProjectDrawer) | `features/<domain>/components/<Parent>/components/<Name>/` |

## Component folder checklist

Every new component folder must contain:
- [ ] `<Name>.tsx` — component logic and JSX
- [ ] `<Name>.css` — scoped styles with camelCase BEM
- [ ] `index.ts` — single line: `export { Name } from './Name';`

## Styles rules

- Import `tokens.css` only in `main.tsx` (once, at app root).
- Each component CSS imports nothing; it uses `var(--token)` variables.
- Class names: camelCase BEM — `.projectRow__status`, `.projectRow--selected`.
- No inline `style={{}}` for layout or color; use CSS classes.

## Imports

```ts
// ✅ Use path aliases
import { Spinner } from '@shared/components/Spinner';
import { useProjects } from '@features/projects/hooks/useProjects';
import { apiRequest } from '@api/client';

// ❌ Never relative cross-feature imports
import { useProjects } from '../../projects/hooks/useProjects';
```

## Adding a new feature — checklist

```
- [ ] Create features/<domain>/ folder
- [ ] Add types.ts with domain types
- [ ] Add api/<domain>ApiClient.ts with typed API functions
- [ ] Add hooks/use<Domain>.ts
- [ ] Add components/ with component folders
- [ ] Add pages/<Page>/ entry point
- [ ] Export public surface in features/<domain>/index.ts
- [ ] Add route to apps/web/src/app/router.tsx
```
